  "prompt": "Can bumble track your location even if you are not active? For example, if you are not currently using the application will it update where you are?",
  "response": "Bumble can track your location in the background if you have granted the app permission to do so in your device settings. However, the app typically only updates your location when:\n\n1. The app is open\n2. You're actively using the app\n3. You've given location permissions in your phone settings\n\nTo prevent background location tracking:\n- On iOS: Go to Settings > Bumble > Location, and select \"While Using the App\"\n- On Android: Go to App Settings > Permissions > Location, and set to \"Only While Using\"\n\nFor the most privacy, you can:\n- Turn off location services for Bumble\n- Use a VPN\n- Disable background app refresh\n- Close the app completely when not in use\n\nIf you want to ensure no location tracking, it's best to review and restrict the app's location permissions on your device.",
